place.name: BOTUS FLEMING
place.gazetteerText: BOTUS-FLEMING, a parish in St. Germans district, Cornwall; near the Hamoaze, 2 miles NW of Saltash r. station. Post Town, Saltash, Cornwall. Acres, 1,138. Real property, £1,329. Pop., 237. Houses, 49. The property is divided among a few. The manor belonged to the Flemings of Stoke-Fleming. The living s a rectory in the diocese of Exeter. Value, £230.* Patron, not reported. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
